From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Patric Stout <github@truebrain.nl>
Date: Fri, 3 Jul 2026 21:41:30 +0200
Subject: [PATCH 13/13] fix: PyChannel_SendException over-decrefs
 caller-supplied value

When value was passed in, args was set to the borrowed 'value' pointer
without an incref. But the function unconditionally Py_DecRef's args
before returning. This over-decremented the caller's object
---
 src/SchedulerModule.cpp | 1 +
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+)

diff --git a/src/SchedulerModule.cpp b/src/SchedulerModule.cpp
index ca1d499..975b4fa 100644
--- a/src/SchedulerModule.cpp
+++ b/src/SchedulerModule.cpp
@@ -651,6 +651,7 @@ extern "C"
 		
         if (value)
         {
+			Py_IncRef( value );
 			args = value;
         }
         else
